	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=600><span id=Guru>PraetorFenix</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>277 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you're dead set on making a half elf paladin, I would have the following statistics as base:<br><br>80 Str<br><b>85 Sta</b> (10 points)<br>90 agi<br>85 Dex<br><b>75 wis</b> (10 points)<br>75 int<br>85 cha<br><br>At level 59 with raid buffs, I hit 255 str, 198 sta, 150 agi, 160 dex, 160 wis, 85 int (who cares?) and 100 cha.<br><br>At my level 1 sta = 5.5 HP, approximately.&nbsp;&nbsp;Those additional 10 points of stamina are a 55 HP difference under raid circumstances.  Name me one person who wouldn't take 55 extra HP with no penalty at high levels.  Even with buffs, I am going to have a very hard time pushing my sta up to the 255 limit.<br><br>The wisdom is due to half elves having VERY poor starting wis.  Since my 750 HP, 225 mana heals tend to add up over time, an extra cast would never hurt in a tight situation.  Again, I'm having a hard time pushing this stat up to the 200 soft cap, even with enchanter buffs.<br><br>Other stats are of little consequence.  Strength I can max in full AC/HP gear with ease, and I only have 90 base.  I still go over the limit.  Useless after level 30.<br><br>Agility over 75 is next to useless.  It does not affect skill rolls for defensive skills (Parry, dodge, etc.).  About 5 agi = 1 AC.  Whoop dee doo.  However if you go under 75 agi you take an AC hit.  But you're a half elf, you have 90 base!  Useless.<br><br>Dexterity influences how often weapons have their effects go off.  Since at my point in the game, <i>everything</i> resists my procs, I give this no weight whatsoever.<br><br>Intelligence is unimportant as skill increases check against your intelligence <b>OR</b> your wisdom.  So you might as well crank up the one that give you more mana.<br><br>Charisma influences your purchase/sell cost of items to/from merchants.  Of course, with about 100 cha and good faction you get the best prices possible.  This is obtainable through cheap gear that you can wear only while buying/selling.  Oh and it increases your charm duration.  Too bad paladins can't charm things.  Useless.<br><br>So there you have my opinion from the high level perspective.</p>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 65th Lord Protector<br>Ascent</td></td></tr>
